articles.description: Virginia strengthened its hold on No. 1 in the AP Top 25, while Duke jumped back into the top five after a pair of impressive wins. Middle Tennessee checked in at 24th, marking its first AP Top 25 appearance in program history.
articles.headline: Virginia stays No. 1 in AP poll; Middle Tennessee makes first-ever appearance

articles.description: North Carolina is putting it all together and the Tar Heels can largely thank their leader, Joel Berry II, for that.
articles.headline: Vitale's weekly awards

articles.description: Eleven SEC teams are within striking distance of the tournament, so what's the problem? They're building their rsums and metrics by beating each other, so the committee might value the league differently when selecting the field.
articles.headline: College hoops Power Rankings: Will SEC's depth help or hurt in March?

articles.description: Over the past decade, the Wildcats have become college basketball's most consistent winner. It started with Jay Wright's cultural rebuild and a whole lot of attitude.
articles.headline: Inside Villanova's epic five-year run

images.caption: Jay Wright (right) has tried to carry on the Villanova culture established by Rollie Massimino.
images.name: Rollie Massimino and Jay Wright [600x400]

images.caption: Kris Jenkins' 3-pointer to beat UNC for a national title was the culmination of Wright's rebuild at Villanova.
images.name: Kris Jenkins [600x600]

images.caption: Donte DiVincenzo and Jalen Brunson combine to score 57 points in Villanova's 86-75 victory over Butler.
images.name: Villanova takes down Butler
